				</gmd:CI_Citation>
			</gmd:citation>
			<gmd:abstract>
				<gco:CharacterString>
					The AQREAN Surface Level dataset provides a comprehensive, high-resolution record of atmospheric composition and meteorology across the United Kingdom, Republic of Ireland, and Northern France. Generated as part of the SPF Clean Air Programme, this reanalysis covers a 17-year period from January 1, 2003, to December 31, 2019. The data is produced using the AQREAN model, a configuration based on the Met Office’s Air Quality in the Unified Model (AQUM), which incorporates the UKCA chemical scheme and CLASSIC aerosol module.

					The dataset offers gridded, hourly surface-level data at a horizontal resolution of 0.1 degree (approximately 10 km) in NetCDF format. It contains a wide array of variables, including primary pollutants (O3, NO, NO2, SO2, CO), particulate matter (PM2.5, PM10) and their chemical components (such as black carbon, sulphate, and ammonium nitrate), and meteorological parameters (including wind speed, temperature, relative humidity, and cloud fractions). Version 1.1 features an enhanced land-sea mask that includes all land areas and small islands, alongside technical corrections for missing end-of-month timesteps and negative precipitation values.
					
					Full details about this dataset can be found at https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/bad1f0f37372421eb777e307b71a28cd
				</gco:CharacterString>
			</gmd:abstract>
			<gmd:purpose>
				<gco:CharacterString>Datasets generated by the Met Office to provide a representation of past pollutant concentrations across the UK.</gco:CharacterString>
			</gmd:purpose>
